<FIRST>r i PM-China-Floods     07-04 0169</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-China-Floods,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>More Than 100 Killed In Flooding in China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A week of flooding in coastal and southern China
has claimed more than 100 lives, left tens of thousands of people
homeless and caused dikes along major rivers to burst, official
reports said today.
   The flooding across five provinces has destroyed thousands of
homes, the China Daily newspaper said, adding that 44 people had
died in Jiangxi province.
   The People's Daily said 31 people were killed and 73 injured in
coastal Zhejiang since torrential rains began falling June 27.
   Areas of western Zhejiang have received between 12 and 20 inches,
and rain was continuing, the paper said.
   Earlier reports said 28 people were killed in southeastern
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and three people died in
Qinghai province, a normally arid region of northwestern China.
   Heavy rains and flooding also have hit Fujian province. State
television has shown people wading through waist-high water.
   Most of the flooded areas were hit last year by severe drought.
</TEXT>
