<HEAD>On the Light Side</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman spent $13,600 to go on a charity date with
Jean LeClerc, who plays heartthrob Jeremy Hunter on ``All My
Children,'' but it won't be an intimate dinner date for two.
   Jan Rogers of Dallas is bringing along a young chaperone _ local
Cystic Fibrosis poster child Mika Doyle.
   ``I thought that was one of the nicest gestures I've ever seen,''
said Regen Horchow Pillsbury, who was one of the organizers of the
Cystic Fibrosis Bachelor Bid held last week.
   Ms. Rogers' donation won her a trip to New York for lunch with
LeClerc at Tavern on the Green and a ringside seat at a taping
session of his popular soap opera.
   Also at Thursday's auction, Dallas socialite Bobbie McKamie paid
$11,500 for a New York date and shopping trip. A few weeks earlier
she had paid $6,500 for country performer George Strait's hat,
according to The Dallas Morning News.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ATTALLA, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   She was a manager at the waffle shop; he
used to eye her on his daily stop.
   Guests showered them with raw grits when they tied the knot.
   She stood near the grill and tossed her bouquet over the counter,
while the kitchen served up dinners like any other night during the
marriage Monday of Sharon Beard, 36, and Randall ``Ray'' Hendrix, 54.
   Beard's sister, restaurant manager Carol Amberson, was maid of
honor. Mrs. Amberson's husband, cook Gary Wayne Amberson, was best
man.
   The wedding procession began in the back near the Waffle House
restaurant's offices.
   Hash browns and uncooked grits, instead of rice, were thrown at
