<HEAD>Weightlifter Dies After Barbells Fall on His Throat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VICTORIA, British Columbia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man bench-pressing 295 pounds
died after dropping the barbell on his throat, authorities said.
   Richard Craig English, a 28-year-old house painter from
Vancouver, died at a hospital Friday. He was working out alone at a
health club and had previously refused offers to use ``spotters'' in
case of an accident, said Detective Sgt. Doug Bond.
   When a club staff member discovered English, ``the barbell was
across his throat and he was blue,'' Bond said Monday.
   ``The night manager told me he had exactly the same thing happen
to him, but he had spotters there, and they pulled the weight off
before any damage was done,'' the detective said.
