<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Yugoslavia-Floods 1stLd-Writethru a0536 07-04 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Yugoslavia-Floods, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0536,0126</SECOND>
<HEAD>Floods Kill 1 in Zagreb, Cause Widespread Damage</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with 5 killed. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAGREB, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Torrential rains triggered floods that
killed five people and inundated 650 homes near Zagreb, state
television reported Tuesday.
   The rain Monday night and early Tuesday was blamed for sweeping a
car off a road into a swollen river near Slovenska Bistrica, about
30 miles west of Zagreb, killing three people, the report said.
   A fisherman drowned near Slovenska Bistrica and a firefighter was
killed in Zagreb, it said.
   Firefighters and other rescue workers evacuated at least 100
people and provided other help to victims in the flood-stricken
area. Damage from the floods was ``enormous,'' according to the
Tanjug news agency.
</TEXT>
