<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Floods     07-04 0104</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Floods,0107</SECOND>
<HEAD>Flooding in East China Kills 47</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A week of heavy rain in eastern China has caused
flooding in three provinces and killed 47 people, official reports
said Tuesday.
   Thousands of homes collapsed and ``countless dams, canals, small
hydroelectric power stations and highways were destroyed,'' the
official Xinhua News Agency said.
   Most of the deaths occurred in Jiangxi province, where 32 people
were killed in flooding from rains that began June 27 and were
expected to continue for several more days. Some areas received
nearly 20 inches of rain, it said.
   Flooding also occurred in Zhejiang and Fujian provinces.
</TEXT>
