<HEAD>London Shares Firmer at Midday Amid Low-Volume Trade</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were firmer at midday Tuesday,
although off the day's best levels, with little news to stir the
market out of light trading.
   Traders said there was little incentive to shift existing
positions, with Wall Street shut Tuesday for the Independence Day
holiday and a drab session anticipated Wednesday due to another
strike by Britain's rail workers and London's bus and subway workers.
   At about noon London time, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange
100-share index was up 9.1 points, or 0.4 percent, to 2,174.7. The
index registered its best level of 2,176.8 by midmorning but slipped
to its low point of 2,172.3 just a half hour later.
   Volume at midday was 224.9 million shares compared with 258.5
million shares at the same time Monday.
