<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Toyota     07-04 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Toyota,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>Toyota to Build Engine Plant in Wales</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japanese car maker Toyota said Tuesday it will
build a $220 million engine plant that will employ 300 people in
north Wales.
   The plant, due to open in Shotton in 1992, would bring
much-needed employment to a town where a steel plant closed in 1980
with the loss of 8,000 jobs.
   Toyota President Shoichiro Toyoda said the company wanted to heed
a European Economic Community proposal that 80 percent of the
content of its cars assembled in Britain be of British origin.
   ``Toyota is determined that our operations in this country should
be truly British and genuinely European,'' Toyoda told a news
conference.
</TEXT>
